text: A compound of six cubes has two forms. One form is a symmetric arrangement of six cubes, considered as square prisms. It is a special case of the compound of six cubes with rotational freedom. Another form is not related to a compound of six cubes with rotational freedom.http://mathworld.wolfram.com/Cube6-Compound.html ==See also== *Compound of three cubes *Compound of five cubes *Compound of four cubes *Compound of six octahedra == References == Category:Polyhedral compounds
